data.enText: a unit for measuring electrical power

tr: a unit of power equal to 1 joule per second
the power dissipated by a current of 1 ampere flowing across a resistance of 1 ohm

value.def: A watt is a unit of measurement of electrical power.

example.ex: Use a 3 amp fuse for equipment up to 720 watts.
example.tran: 720 瓦以下的设备使用3安培的保险丝。
